OL,6,FWhile, she said, Sharkey's offending
OL,7,Fcrossed the custody threshold, she
OL,8,Fbelieved she "presented no danger or
OL,9,Frisk to the public".
OL,11,FPolice bodycam footage shows the
OL,12,Fmoment Joanne Sharkey was arrested on
OL,13,Fsuspicion of killing and concealing
OL,14,Fthe birth of her baby boy in 1998.
OL,16,FHanding her two years in prison,
OL,17,Fsuspended for two years, Mrs Justice
OL,18,FEady said: "I cannot avoid the
OL,19,Fconclusion that a custodial term is
OL,20,Fthe appropriate disposal.
